    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-01-16T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-01-16T14:00:00-05:00" n="444"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d444">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 351.117/5.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Ambassador <persName type="to">Herrick</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-01-16T14:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 16, 1914, 2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your despatch No. 494, of January 2, concerning Joseph Nouguier. The Department
                    understands the conflict between the laws of France and the United States as to
                    naturalization; nevertheless desires that the attention of the French Government
                    be called to the facts of Nouguier’s naturalization in this country and
                    appointment as postmaster, and that the representations set forth in its
                    telegram of December 27 be made.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
